---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import SharpWalkthrough from '../components/SharpWalkthrough.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<BaseLayout title="About A-Worthy | NUS Law Graduate Tutor, Singapore" description="Founded by an NUS Law graduate, A-Worthy brings legal-analytical precision to O-Level English & Maths, GP & H2 Economics tuition. Discover the SHARP Method.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
  <section class="hero about-hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <span class="eyebrow">About A-Worthy</span>
      <h1>Singapore&rsquo;s analytical tuition centre &mdash; where legal precision meets academic results</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="marquee" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="marquee-inner">
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> Legal Precision</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> O-Level English</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> The SHARP Method</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> H1 General Paper</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> A-Worthy</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> H2 Economics</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> Founded by a Law Graduate</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> Analytical Mastery</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> O-Level English</span>
      <span class="marquee-item"><span class="marquee-dot"></span> The SHARP Method</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== OUR STORY ===== -->
  <section class="section story">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="story-layout">
        <div class="story-text" data-animate="reveal-up">
          <span class="eyebrow">Our Story</span>
          <h2>A letter from our founder</h2>
          <p>Dear parents,</p>
          <p>
            People ask me why I left law to teach tuition. The honest answer is I didn&rsquo;t really leave &mdash; I just found a better use for the training.
          </p>
          <p>
            I graduated from NUS Law and went straight into corporate work. IPO listings, prospectuses, regulatory filings. The kind of work where you read the same 200-page document five times because one wrong line means the whole deal falls apart. I was good at it. I was also miserable.
          </p>
          <p>
            The thing that kept me sane was tutoring. I&rsquo;d started during uni just to earn some extra money, and somehow never stopped. I&rsquo;d leave the office, sit down with a student&rsquo;s exam paper, and feel more awake in that hour than I had all day. My wife will tell you I talked about my students more than my cases.
          </p>
          <p>
            But here&rsquo;s what I couldn&rsquo;t shake. I kept meeting the same student &mdash; different name, different school, same problem. Smart kid. Studied hard. Could explain the answer to me perfectly across the table. But the moment they sat down for an exam, something went wrong. The ideas were there. The marks weren&rsquo;t.
          </p>
          <p>
            It took me a while to figure out why. In law school, they drill a process into you from week one: read precisely, find the right framework, apply it to the facts, check your work. You do it so many times it becomes automatic. That&rsquo;s how you survive &mdash; whether it&rsquo;s a contract law exam or a billion-dollar prospectus.
          </p>
          <p>
            One night I was marking a GP essay and it hit me. I&rsquo;d been teaching that same process to my students without realising it. The ones who improved weren&rsquo;t studying more. They were thinking more precisely &mdash; the way I&rsquo;d been trained to think in law.
          </p>
          <p>
            So I wrote it down. Five steps. I called it SHARP. It wasn&rsquo;t some big eureka moment. It was more like finally putting a name to something I&rsquo;d been doing all along.
          </p>
          <p>
            Leaving law was harder than I expected &mdash; not the work, but the conversations. My parents didn&rsquo;t say much, which in a Singaporean family means they had a lot to say. My colleagues were polite about it, which was worse. An NUS law degree is supposed to lead somewhere specific, and &ldquo;tuition teacher&rdquo; isn&rsquo;t it.
          </p>
          <p>
            But I&rsquo;d seen what happens when a student learns to approach a paper with a system instead of just hope. I couldn&rsquo;t unsee it.
          </p>
          <p>
            I also made plenty of mistakes early on. My first classes were too big. I thought I could help more students by fitting more into a room. What actually happened was that the quiet ones disappeared. They&rsquo;d nod along, hand in their work, and I wouldn&rsquo;t catch their mistakes until it was too late. So I set a rule: six students, maximum. It means I teach fewer students. It also means I actually know each one &mdash; where they lose marks, what they&rsquo;re avoiding, what clicks for them and what doesn&rsquo;t.
          </p>
          <p>
            Today I teach students from all over Singapore. Some come from Raffles and Hwa Chong. Some come from neighbourhood schools. Honestly, the gap between them is never about how smart they are. It&rsquo;s about whether anyone has shown them a system for translating what they know into what the examiner wants to see.
          </p>
          <p>
            I became a father recently. And I&rsquo;ll be honest &mdash; it&rsquo;s changed how I see what I do. I used to think of my students as someone else&rsquo;s children. Now I think about what kind of teacher I&rsquo;d want for my own. That&rsquo;s the standard I hold myself to.
          </p>
          <p>
            If that sounds like your child &mdash; knows the content, puts in the hours, but the grades don&rsquo;t reflect it &mdash; I think we can help.
          </p>
          <p class="founder-sign-off">
            &mdash; Jeremy<br />
            Founder, A-Worthy
          </p>
        </div>
        <aside class="founder-card" data-animate="reveal-up">
          <div class="founder-card__photo" aria-label="Jeremy Lim, Founder of A-Worthy">
            <svg aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <defs>
                <linearGradient id="founder-gradient" x1="0" y1="0" x2="1" y2="1">
                  <stop offset="0%" stop-color="rgba(212, 133, 58, 0.15)" />
                  <stop offset="100%" stop-color="rgba(43, 90, 140, 0.12)" />
                </linearGradient>
              </defs>
              <rect width="200" height="200" rx="100" fill="url(#founder-gradient)"/>
              <circle cx="100" cy="80" r="32" fill="rgba(43, 90, 140, 0.2)"/>
              <ellipse cx="100" cy="155" rx="50" ry="38" fill="rgba(43, 90, 140, 0.15)"/>
            </svg>
            <span class="founder-card__initials">JL</span>
          </div>
          <div class="founder-card__body">
            <span class="founder-card__name">Jeremy Lim</span>
            <span class="founder-card__role">Founder &amp; Lead Tutor</span>
            <ul class="founder-card__creds">
              <li>NUS Faculty of Law &mdash; LLB (Hons)</li>
              <li>500+ students taught since 2020</li>
              <li>Creator of the SHARP Method</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/contact/" class="founder-card__cta btn btn-accent">Book a Free Assessment</a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== WHAT WE TEACH ===== -->
  <section class="section subjects">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow" data-animate="reveal-up">What We Teach</span>
      <h2 data-animate="reveal-up">Five subjects, one proven tuition framework</h2>

      <div class="values-grid">
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="1">
          <h3>O-Level English</h3>
          <p>
            For Sec 1&ndash;4 students. Comprehension, composition, oral, and editing &mdash;
            every component taught through the SHARP Method, with paper-matched frameworks at the Hit step. Foundation and intensive programmes available.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="2">
          <h3>O-Level Mathematics</h3>
          <p>
            For Sec 1&ndash;4 students. Algebra, geometry, trigonometry, functions, statistics, and probability &mdash; each topic area taught with a named framework (READ, LABEL, PLOT, DATA, RULE, SHOW) that maps directly to the 4048 mark scheme.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="3">
          <h3>Pre-IB Mathematics</h3>
          <p>
            For Year 3 &amp; Year 4 (pre-IB) students. Indices, surds, algebra, logarithms, trigonometry, and an introduction to calculus &mdash; taught with the SHARP Method and annotated, line-by-line working that IB examiners reward.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="4">
          <h3>H1 General Paper</h3>
          <p>
            For JC 1&ndash;2 students. Essay argumentation, comprehension, and AQ mastery across all
            12 content themes. The SHARP Method&rsquo;s analytical roots make it a natural fit for GP.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="5">
          <h3>H2 Economics</h3>
          <p>
            For JC 1&ndash;2 students. Diagram precision, essay technique, and case study mastery
            covering the full 9570 syllabus. Analytical rigour applied to economic reasoning.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="6">
          <h3>One-to-One Coaching</h3>
          <p>
            Available across all five subjects. Fully customised to the student&rsquo;s specific gaps,
            with flexible scheduling and personalised feedback every session.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== THE FOUNDER ===== -->
  <section class="section team">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow" data-animate="reveal-up">The Founder</span>
      <h2 data-animate="reveal-up">Legal mind, teaching heart</h2>

      <div class="founder-profile" data-animate="reveal-up">
        <div class="founder-photo-wrap">
          <div class="founder-photo-placeholder" aria-label="Founder photo">
            <svg aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="200" height="200">
              <rect width="200" height="200" rx="100" fill="rgba(43,90,140,0.08)"/>
              <circle cx="100" cy="75" r="35" fill="rgba(43,90,140,0.15)"/>
              <ellipse cx="100" cy="155" rx="55" ry="40" fill="rgba(43,90,140,0.12)"/>
              <text x="100" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Nunito, sans-serif" font-size="10" fill="rgba(43,90,140,0.4)" letter-spacing="0.1em">PHOTO</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="founder-signature" aria-hidden="true">Jeremy Lim</div>
        </div>
        <div class="founder-info">
          <span class="eyebrow">Meet the Founder</span>
          <h3>Jeremy Lim &mdash; NUS Law Graduate &amp; Educator</h3>
          <p>With a law degree from NUS and years of direct teaching experience, Jeremy asked a simple question: why do law students learn to think so precisely, but secondary and JC students are told to &ldquo;just practise more&rdquo;? The answer became the SHARP Method &mdash; a five-step system (See, Hit, Apply, Refine, Practise) that distils legal-analytical rigour into a repeatable framework any student can master. Paper-matched frameworks are deployed at the Hit step, producing the kind of structured thinking that examiners reward with top grades.</p>
          <div class="founder-credentials">
            <span class="founder-credential"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg> NUS Faculty of Law</span>
            <span class="founder-credential"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg> 500+ Students Taught</span>
            <span class="founder-credential"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg> SHARP Method Creator</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== VALUES ===== -->
  <section class="section values">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow" data-animate="reveal-up">Our Values</span>
      <h2 data-animate="reveal-up">The pillars that define who we are</h2>

      <div class="values-grid">
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="1">
          <h3>Analytical Precision</h3>
          <p>
            Other tuition centres teach content. We teach the thinking process behind the content. The same rigour that trains lawyers to win cases trains your child to win marks &mdash; systematically, across every exam component.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="2">
          <h3>Proven Results</h3>
          <p>
            90% A1&ndash;B3 rate. Students going from D7 to A2 in three months. We don&rsquo;t make vague promises &mdash; we track every student&rsquo;s progress against official marking criteria and show you the numbers.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="3">
          <h3>Small Groups</h3>
          <p>
            Six students maximum. No exceptions. Your child can&rsquo;t be invisible in a class this small &mdash; they get live feedback on their work every session, and the tutor knows their specific strengths and weaknesses by name.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-item card--accent-left" data-animate="reveal-up" data-animate-delay="4">
          <h3>The SHARP Method</h3>
          <p>
            See, Hit, Apply, Refine, Practise &mdash; five steps your child follows for every question, every subject, every exam. Paper-matched frameworks are deployed at the Hit step, giving students precise tools for each paper type. It&rsquo;s not a gimmick; it&rsquo;s a repeatable system that compounds over time, turning analytical thinking into exam results.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== SHARP WALKTHROUGH (interactive) ===== -->
  <SharpWalkthrough />

  <!-- ===== ONLINE DELIVERY ===== -->
  <section class="section centres">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow" data-animate="reveal-up">Online Delivery</span>
      <h2 data-animate="reveal-up">100% Online Delivery</h2>

      <div class="centres-grid">
        <div class="centre-card card--elevated" data-animate="reveal-up">
          <h3>Learn from anywhere in Singapore</h3>
          <p>
            All lessons are conducted via Zoom Pro with cloud recording, screen sharing, and
            breakout rooms. Students join from anywhere in Singapore. No commute, no wasted
            time &mdash; just focused learning.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== CTA ===== -->
  <section class="section cta">
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow" data-animate="reveal-up">Get Started</span>
      <h2 data-animate="reveal-up">Book a free diagnostic assessment</h2>
      <p class="cta-desc">
        A 20-minute session analysing your child&rsquo;s recent paper &mdash; English, Maths, GP, or Economics.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="cta-button">Book Free Assessment</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Jeremy Lim",
    "jobTitle": "Founder & Lead Tutor",
    "worksFor": {
      "@type": "EducationalOrganization",
      "name": "A-Worthy",
      "url": "https://a-worthy.com"
    },
    "alumniOf": {
      "@type": "CollegeOrUniversity",
      "name": "National University of Singapore, Faculty of Law"
    },
    "hasCredential": "LLB (Hons), NUS Faculty of Law",
    "description": "Founder of A-Worthy and creator of the SHARP Method. NUS Law graduate teaching O-Level English, O-Level Mathematics, H1 General Paper, and H2 Economics in Singapore.",
    "knowsAbout": ["O-Level English Tuition", "O-Level Mathematics Tuition", "H1 General Paper Tuition", "H2 Economics Tuition", "SHARP Method", "Examination Technique"],
    "url": "https://a-worthy.com/about/"
  })} />

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ===== DESIGN TOKENS ===== */
  :root {
    --about-bg: var(--bg-primary);
    --about-bg-alt: var(--bg-secondary);
    --about-white: #ffffff;
    --about-gray: var(--text-secondary);
    --about-border: var(--border-color);
    --about-accent: var(--color-accent);
    --about-font: var(--font-body);
    --about-mono: var(--font-mono);
  }

  /* ===== EYEBROW ===== */
  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--about-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--about-accent);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* ===== HERO ===== */
  .hero {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-primary) 0%, var(--bg-secondary) 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-hero { position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .about-hero::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -30%;
    left: -10%;
    width: 500px;
    height: 500px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(212, 133, 58, 0.08) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hero-content {
    max-width: 1200px;
    width: 100%;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .hero-content h1 {
    font-family: var(--about-font);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 200;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  /* ===== SECTIONS ===== */
  .section {
    background: var(--about-bg);
    padding: 1.75rem 0;
  }

  .section:nth-child(even) {
    background: var(--about-bg-alt);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-family: var(--about-font);
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.4rem);
    font-weight: 200;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 0 3rem;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .section p {
    font-family: var(--about-font);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--about-gray);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ===== OUR STORY ===== */
  .story-text h2 {
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  /* ===== VALUES ===== */
  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .value-item {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  @media (hover: hover) {
    .value-item:hover {
      transform: translateY(-3px);
      border-color: rgba(26, 42, 58, 0.12);
    }
  }

  .value-item h3 {
    font-family: var(--about-font);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .value-item p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ===== CENTRES ===== */
  .centres-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .centre-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  @media (hover: hover) {
    .centre-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-3px);
      border-color: rgba(26, 42, 58, 0.12);
    }
  }

  .centre-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--about-font);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .centre-card p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ===== CTA ===== */
  .section.cta {
    background: var(--about-bg-alt);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .cta-inner {
    max-width: 600px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .cta h2 {
    max-width: 100%;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cta .cta-desc {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .cta-button {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--about-font);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    background: var(--color-accent);
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    padding: 0.9rem 2.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .cta-button:hover {
    opacity: 0.9;
    transform: translateY(-3px);
  }

  /* ===== FOUNDER PROFILE ===== */
  .founder-profile {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: #FFFDF6;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7) inset,
      0 1px 2px rgba(26, 42, 58, 0.04),
      0 14px 30px -22px rgba(26, 42, 58, 0.18);
  }
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .founder-profile {
    background: var(--bg-card);
  }
  .founder-photo-wrap {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .founder-photo-placeholder {
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 2px solid var(--border-color);
  }
  /* Pinyon Script signature — used deliberately once (claudedesign H.2). */
  .founder-signature {
    font-family: 'Pinyon Script', cursive;
    font-size: 2.4rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-top: 1rem;
    opacity: 0.85;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .founder-info h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .founder-info p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .founder-credentials {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .founder-credential {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
